title: New Chairperson of Council on Human Reproductive Technology appointed
content_text:
p>
    The Government announced today (March 26) the appointment of Mr Gregory 
    Leung Wing-lup as the chairperson of the Council on Human Reproductive 
    Technology (CHRT) for two years with effect from April 11, 2010.  Commenting on the appointment, the Secretary for Food and Health, Dr York 
    Chow, said: "Mr Leung has extensive experience in public services with 
    proven leadership skills. He supervised the drafting and introduction into 
    the Legislative Council of the Human Reproductive Technology Bill in 1999

the Legislative Council of the Human Reproductive Technology Bill in 1999 
    when he served as the Deputy Secretary for Health and Welfare from April 
    1997 to April 2001. "With his rich knowledge about the Human Reproductive Technology Ordinance 
    and its policy context, I am fully confident that Mr Leung will be able to 
    lead the CHRT to perform its statutory functions." Dr Chow also thanked the outgoing chairperson, Dr Leong Che-hung.  "I would like to express my sincere gratitude for Dr Leong's indispensable

contribution to the regulation of the human reproductive technology 
    activities in Hong Kong ever since 1987 when he chaired the then Committee 
    on Scientifically Assisted Human Reproduction. He assumed membership of the 
    Provisional Council on Reproductive Technology in 1995, and has provided 
    nine years of excellent leadership to the CHRT as its founding chairperson 
    since its establishment in 2001.  "Dr Leong has led the CHRT in the drafting of the regulations under the 
    ordinance, the preparation of the Code of Practice on Reproductive

ordinance, the preparation of the Code of Practice on Reproductive 
    Technology and Embryo Research, and the design and implementation of the 
    licensing system for human reproductive technology activities. His unfailing 
    effort has laid a solid foundation for the future work of the CHRT."
